Dobson et. al. "The combination of a signal and one or more delayed versions of it is arguably the single most important process in the repertoire of the audio programmer."

Goals:
    Learn how to describe a delay effect (and, consequently, almost any effect) in terms of the passage of a single sample through a delay line.

    